section.section:
Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection and subsection (d) of this section, the subdivision regulations may include provisions for:
the harmonious development of the regional district;
the coordination of roads within the subdivision with:
existing planned or platted roads;
features of the regional district;
that county's general plan; or
a transportation plan adopted by the Commission as part of that county's general plan;
adequate open spaces for transportation, recreation, light, and air, by dedication or otherwise;
the dedication to public use or conveyance of areas designated for dedication under the zoning and subdivision regulations; and
in lieu of dedication, the payment of a monetary fee that meets the requirements of subsection (d) of this section;
the reservation of land for:
public buildings, including schools;
parks and playgrounds;
roads;
mass transit facilities, including busways or light rail facilities; and
any other public purpose;
the conservation or production of adequate transportation, water drainage, and sanitary facilities;
the preservation of the location of, the volume and flow of water in, and other characteristics of natural streams and other waterways, including the establishment of a stormwater management program in Montgomery County for the purpose of:
allowing the county to accept monetary contributions;
granting an easement; or
dedicating land;
the avoidance of undue population congestion;
the avoidance of a scattered or premature subdivision that otherwise may:
result in danger or injury to health, safety, or welfare due to the lack of water supply, drainage, transportation, or other public services; or
necessitate an excessive expenditure of public funds for the supply of services;
the conformity of resubdivided lots to the character of lots within the existing subdivision with respect to area, frontage, and alignment to existing lots and roads;
except for agricultural or recreational purposes, the control of subdivision or building in floodplain areas and in streams and drainage courses, and on unsafe land areas;
the preservation of outstanding natural or cultural features and historic sites or structures;
any benefit to the health, comfort, safety, or welfare of the present and future population of the regional district;
the extent and manner to which the following actions shall be taken before the approval of a plat:
the grading and improvement of roads;
the building of curbs, gutters, and sidewalks;
the installation of water, sewer, and other utility mains, piping, connections, and facilities; and
the planting or conservation of trees; or
in Montgomery County:
adequate recreational facilities; or
in lieu of providing recreational facilities, the payment of a fee that does not exceed the cost of providing adequate recreational facilities to serve the subdivision.
